<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-09-26T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-09-26T14:00:00-05:00" n="635" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d635">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">760F.62/1147f: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Czechoslovakia</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Carr</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-09-26T14:00:00-05:00">September 26, 1938—2
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>72. Your 234, September 25, 1 p.m. The President early this morning sent
                            identical messages to Mr. Beneš, Chancellor Hitler, and Prime Ministers
                            Chamberlain and Daladier, which were immediately made available to the
                            press. This should be construed as in the nature of a reply by the
                            President to the message sent him through you Saturday [<hi rend="italic">Sunday</hi>] last.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>